Environment: Linux/VIM
How to make project: make

Example of how to run project: ./oss -n 3 -s 3 -t 4.2 -i 0.6

Usage: Program runs a simulated clock to track a Process Control Table and processes shared with a worker file (child process)and the oss.c file. Both files share the same memory with clock time simulated. Program will only accept those arguements above. You can run just -n, it will only run for 60 seconds top regardless of the arguments passed above. Then terminated with shared memory released.  

./oss [-n proc] [-s simul] [-t timeLimitForChildren] [-i interval]

-n proc, sets total number of children to launch.
-s simul, max number of children running simultaneously.
-t timeLimit, time limit for childen processes set in seconds e.g 4.5.
-i interval of seconds for children processes to launch in seconds e.g. 0.5 seconds.

